documentation.value:
Parse command-line options.

```bash
while getopts ":hv:f:" opt; do
    case $opt in
        h) usage ;;
        v) verbose=1 ;;
        f) file="$OPTARG" ;;
        \?) echo "Invalid: -$OPTARG" ;;
        :) echo "Missing arg: -$OPTARG" ;;
    esac
done
shift $((OPTIND - 1))
```

completions.insertText:
while getopts ":${1:hv:f:}" opt; do
	case \$opt in
		${2:h}) ${3:usage} ;;
		${4:v}) ${5:verbose=1} ;;
		${6:f}) ${7:file="\$OPTARG"} ;;
		\\?) echo "Invalid option: -\$OPTARG" >&2; exit 1 ;;
		:) echo "Option -\$OPTARG requires an argument" >&2; exit 1 ;;
	esac
done
shift \$((OPTIND - 1))

documentation.value:
Simple logging functions.

```bash
log()  { echo "[$(date +'%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] $*"; }
warn() { log "WARN: $*" >&2; }
err()  { log "ERROR: $*" >&2; }
```

